[src:ppo-algorithm/markov-decision-process] for all feasible solution $y(i,a)$ to the D-LP.
[src:ppo-algorithm/markov-decision-process] Once we have found the optimal solution $y^{*}(i,a)$ , we can use it to establish the optimal policies.
[src:ppo-algorithm/markov-decision-process] In continuous-time MDP, if the state space and action space are continuous, the optimal criterion could be found by solving the Hamilton–Jacobi–Bellman (HJB) partial differential equation.
